SUMMARY:[Registries of Deeds] Page updated: Kennebec County Registry of De
 eds
DESCRIPTION:This page's content changed since the last check. Visit the pa
 ge directly to review the update.\n\nWhat changed (text excerpt):\nAdded:\
 n  + Registry of Deeds\n  + The Kennebec County Registry of Deeds has prou
 dly served our community since 1799\, safeguarding the essential property 
 records that form the foundation of real estate ownership.\n  + As require
 d by Maine law\, the Registry meticulously maintains and preserves all rec
 orded documents and plans from historical deeds dating back over 200 years
  to today’s modern transactions.\n  + Our office provides prompt\, profe
 ssional\, and courteous service to the public\, making vital records such 
 as mortgages\, deeds\, liens\, and plans easily accessible. Every document
  is carefully preserved for the permanent record.\n  + Records are availab
 le for convenient public search both online and in our office\, supporting
  homeowners\, real estate professionals\, title companies\, and businesses
  throughout Kennebec County.\n  + The Registry is led by Register of Deeds
  Matthew Boucher\, with dedicated support from Deputy Register Sue Lapoint
 e and a committed team.\n  + Whether you’re researching property history
 \, closing a real estate transaction\, or ensuring clear title\, the Kenne
 bec County Registry of Deeds stands ready to serve you with accuracy\, eff
 iciency\, and a strong commitment to customer service.\n  + Property Alert
 \n  + SIGN UP NOW\n  + Search\n  + Public Records\nRemoved:\n  - Click her
 e to search\n  - public records\n  - Click here to sign up for property al
 ert\n  - Matthew Boucher\n  - Register of Deeds\nhttps://kennebec.gov/deed
 s/
URL:https://kennebec.gov/deeds/
CATEGORIES:Registries of Deeds
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
